This paper focuses on the analysis of bibliometric data related to global corporate research and development activities, which involves the use of information technology and data analysis techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which deals with the management, organization, and retrieval of digital information. The paper also involves the use of data mining and analysis techniques, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category cs.SD (Software Development), as it involves the development of software tools for data analysis and visualization.
